history.content: As per @3340, we are unable to advise on Cal Central concerns. Please contact SIS

So I have a bit of an interesting problem with Cal Central enrollments.  I initially signed up for EE16B and used the swap functionality to say that if I got off the waitlist for Math 104, I would want to be put in that class instead.  But I've since rethought my schedule, and I want to take both 16B and 104.  Is there a way for me to cancel the swap?  I would prefer to not drop and readd 104, since there are no open spots, and I don't want to run the risk that someone takes my spot before I can sign up again.  I would feel a bit safer dropping and readding 16B, but I'm not sure if that would actually help.

(If it matters, I did have to change which sections I was signed up for in 16B in order to make sure the two classes didn't conflict.  Not sure if this would cancel the swap on its own, but it would be nice to know if it did)
history.subject: Undoing a swap on Cal Central
